    <!-- Chosen Palette: Slate & Amber -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is designed as a narrative journey for an MBA student, moving from high-level summary to deep analysis. The structure is thematic, not linear like the report, to enhance understanding. It starts with a 'Hero' section for immediate context. A sticky navigation allows users to jump to specific areas of interest: 'The Journey' (interactive timeline), 'The Transformation' (core strategic analysis of why, how, challenges, and opportunities), and 'Case Insights' (actionable Q&A for the student). This user-centric flow was chosen to break down a complex business case into digestible, interactive modules, facilitating exploration and learning over passive reading. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Report Info: Case Timeline -> Goal: Show chronological progression -> Viz/Method: Interactive horizontal timeline (HTML/CSS/JS) -> Interaction: Click on dates to reveal details -> Justification: More engaging and space-efficient than a static list.
        - Report Info: RBI Eligibility Criteria -> Goal: Compare AU SFB's metrics against requirements -> Viz/Method: Bar Chart (Chart.js) -> Interaction: Hover tooltips for precise data -> Justification: Instantly visualizes compliance and outperformance, superior to a static table.
        - Report Info: Strategic Rationale -> Goal: Inform on key drivers -> Viz/Method: Icon-driven card layout (HTML/Tailwind) -> Interaction: Hover effects for engagement -> Justification: Quickly communicates core concepts visually.
        - Report Info: Challenges & Enablers -> Goal: Compare pros and cons -> Viz/Method: Side-by-side list with toggles (HTML/JS) -> Interaction: Click to expand/collapse details -> Justification: Encourages deeper exploration of the central strategic tension.
        - Report Info: Discussion Questions -> Goal: Organize study points -> Viz/Method: Accordion UI (HTML/JS) -> Interaction: Click to reveal analysis points -> Justification: Directly serves the MBA student's need to prepare for case discussion in a clean, organized manner.
        - Library/Method: Chart.js for canvas-based charts. All other visuals are structured HTML/CSS with Tailwind. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
